FBIS4-40963 "drsov119_b_94035" FBIS-SOV-94-119 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Unprofitable Coal Mines To Be Closed Down Unprofitable Coal Mines To Be Closed Down PM2106094394 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 17 Jun 94 p 1 PM2106094394 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN [Report by INTERFAX: "Unprofitable Mines Will Be Closed"] [Text] This year Russia will earmark 305 billion rubles for closing unprofitable coal mines. For the first time the Russian state budget envisages a separate category for expenditure on such objectives. In the near future, according to "Rosugol" Company Deputy Chairman N. Garkavenko, there are plans to complete work on closing down five unprofitable pits, including pits in the Pechora coal field. Another six pits will be shut down before the end of 1995.
